        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 8:53PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 853 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Chesterfield Court
House to 9 miles southeast of Moseley to near Mannboro. Movement was
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, heavy rain, and frequent
lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Reduced visibility and minor flooding
possible. Frequent cloud to ground lightning strikes.

Locations impacted include...
Chester, Bellwood, Sutherland, Chesterfield Court House, Matoaca,
Chesterfield, Ammon, Pocahontas State Park, Church Road, Beach, Five
Forks, Drewrys Bluff, and Centralia.
</description>
        <instruction>Heavy rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
